59int
60cmd_lookup(int argc, char *argv[])
61{
62 struct nb_ctx *ctx;
63 struct sockaddr *sap;
64 char *hostname;
65 int error, opt;
66
67 if (argc < 2)
68 lookup_usage();
69 error = nb_ctx_create(&ctx);
70 if (error) {
71 smb_error("unable to create nbcontext", error);
72 exit(1);
73 }
74 if (smb_open_rcfile() == 0) {
75 if (nb_ctx_readrcsection(smb_rc, ctx, "default", 0) != 0)
76 exit(1);
77 rc_close(smb_rc);
78 }
79 while ((opt = getopt(argc, argv, "w:")) != EOF) {
80 switch(opt){
81 case 'w':
82 nb_ctx_setns(ctx, optarg);
83 break;
84 default:
85 lookup_usage();
86 /*NOTREACHED*/
87 }
88 }
89 if (optind >= argc)
90 lookup_usage();
91 if (nb_ctx_resolve(ctx) != 0)
92 exit(1);
93 hostname = argv[argc - 1];
94/* printf("Looking for %s...\n", hostname);*/
95 error = nbns_resolvename(hostname, ctx, &sap);
96 if (error) {
97 smb_error("unable to resolve %s", error, hostname);
98 exit(1);
99 }
100 printf("Got response from %s\n", inet_ntoa(ctx->nb_lastns.sin_addr));
101 printf("IP address of %s: %s\n", hostname, inet_ntoa(((struct sockaddr_in*)sap)->sin_addr));
102 return 0;
103}
104
105
106void
107lookup_usage(void)
108{
109 fprintf(stderr, "Usage: %s lookup [-w host] name\n", getprogname());
110 exit(1);
111}
